niou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>· d(is) · m(anibus) · \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Asinia Char\n                    mosyne\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Asinia\">Asinia\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Char\n                    mosyne\">Char-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>mosyne\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · v(ixit) · a(nnis) · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>LXV · mens(ibus) · · \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Mallianus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Mallianus\">Mallianus\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>fil(ius) ❦ fec(it) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>·D·M·\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Asinia Char\n                    mosyne\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Asinia\">ASINIA\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Char\n                    mosyne\">CHAR\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>MOSYNE\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·V·A·\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>LXV·MENS··\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">VII\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Mallianus\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Mallianus\">MALLIANUS\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>FIL❦FEC\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000694_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000694_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000694.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-07-14\" src=\"ISic000694-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy (earlier editions did not note interpuncts, hedera, or supraline)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"5\">5: \u003Cspan>Manganaro: M.Allianus\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the shades of the underworld, Asinia Charmosyne lived for 65 years and 7 months. Mallianus, her son, set this up.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Solin rejects Manganaro's reading of MALLIENUS in line 5 as M(arcus) Allienus, partly because the absence of a gentilicium would be odd and partly because of the absence of an interpunct after the M (which autopsy confirms to be absent). Fasolo repeats Manganaro's text.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 1991.0901 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 1989.0338n \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1989 165 no.22 fig.22 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001831\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Solin 1990 134 no.139 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001422\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001422\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Fasolo 2013 85 no.33 fig.59 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002011\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Deep v-cut letters with simple terminal serifs. Some letters tending to curved, particularly V, but also tail to F; L and I almost indistinguishable. Simple dash interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1-2  31-32  Line 3-4  28-31  Line 5  22-29  Line 6  15-16 (F tail to 19)  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[283,286,289,292,295,298